contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:38.742 --> 02:41.160
Mrs. Peterson!

02:41.244 --> 02:43.579
Ramon, hey! How's it goin'?

02:43.664 --> 02:45.998
How you doin'?

02:46.083 --> 02:48.125
There it is,
right there on the desk.

02:48.210 --> 02:51.545
- Where's she headed?
- She's snowbound, Ramon.

02:55.425 --> 02:58.302
- See you went with the pink.
- Yeah, yeah.

02:58.387 --> 03:00.513
It's kind of a pink day today.

03:00.597 --> 03:03.474
I'm gonna have another pickup
for you on Thursday.

03:03.558 --> 03:05.726
- All right. We'll see you then.
- All right. Thanks, Ramon.

03:40.971 --> 03:43.639
Peterson! Peterson!

03:44.975 --> 03:47.059
Peterson.

03:49.646 --> 03:52.314
- Mr. Cowboy, da?
- Da.

03:56.820 --> 03:59.864
Mmm, it's pretty.

03:59.948 --> 04:03.033
Mmm. It's from my wife.

05:09.559 --> 05:11.519
Time...

05:11.603 --> 05:13.938
rules over us without mercy...

05:14.022 --> 05:17.775
not caring if we're healthy or ill,
hungry or drunk...

05:17.859 --> 05:21.487
Russian, American,
beings from Mars.

05:21.571 --> 05:24.490
It's like a fire.
It could either destroy us or keep us warm.

05:24.574 --> 05:27.243
That's why every FedEx office
has a clock.

05:27.327 --> 05:30.162
Because we live or we die
by the clock.

05:30.247 --> 05:32.164
We never turn our back on it.

05:32.249 --> 05:34.291
And we never, ever
allow ourselves...

05:34.376 --> 05:37.670
the sin of losing track
of time!

05:37.754 --> 05:39.839
Locally, it's 1:56.

05:39.923 --> 05:43.759
That means we've got
three hours and four minutes...

05:43.844 --> 05:45.761
before the end-of-the-day's
package sort.

05:45.846 --> 05:48.014
That's how long we have.
That's how much time we have...

05:50.267 --> 05:53.185
before this pulsating, accursed,
relentless taskmaster...

05:53.270 --> 05:55.855
tries to put us
out of business.

05:55.939 --> 05:59.024
Hey, Nicolai. Hey.
Nicolai, good to see you.

05:59.109 --> 06:00.985
How are you, kid?
Look what you did.

06:01.069 --> 06:03.195
You just delivered
your very first FedEx package.

06:03.280 --> 06:06.866
That deserves something special,
like a Snickers bar...

06:06.950 --> 06:09.785
and a C.D. player.

06:09.870 --> 06:11.787
And something to listen to...
a C.D. There.

06:11.872 --> 06:14.665
Elvis Presley. Fifty million fans
can't be wrong.

06:14.749 --> 06:16.667
You all recognize this,
don't you?

06:16.751 --> 06:19.461
I took the liberty
of sending this to myself.

06:19.546 --> 06:24.508
I FedEx'd it
before I left Memphis.

06:24.593 --> 06:26.719
You're probably wondering
what could be in here.

06:26.803 --> 06:29.138
What could it possibly be?
Is it architectural plans?

06:29.222 --> 06:31.140
Maybe technical drawings?

06:31.224 --> 06:33.976
Is this the new wallpaper
for the... for the bathroom?

06:36.062 --> 06:38.814
It is... a clock...

06:38.899 --> 06:40.816
which I started
at absolute zero...

06:40.901 --> 06:45.863
and is now at 87 hours,
22 minutes and 17 seconds.

06:45.947 --> 06:50.826
From Memphis, America
to Nicolai in Russia, 87 hours.

06:50.911 --> 06:54.121
Eighty-seven hours
is a shameful outrage.

06:54.205 --> 06:57.249
This is just an egg timer!

06:57.334 --> 07:00.085
What if it had been something else?
Like your paycheck?

07:00.170 --> 07:01.734
Or fresh boysenberries?
Or adoption papers?

07:03.381 --> 07:05.424
Eighty-seven hours
is an eternity.

07:05.508 --> 07:07.468
The cosmos was created
in less time!

07:07.552 --> 07:10.346
Wars have been fought and
nations toppled in 87 hours!

07:10.430 --> 07:12.348
Fortunes made and squandered.

07:16.561 --> 07:18.479
What?

07:18.563 --> 07:20.481
What are you saying about me?

07:20.565 --> 07:22.483
I tell them,
what do they expect?

07:22.567 --> 07:26.278
This man, when his truck broke down, he
stole a boy's bicycle to do his delivery.

07:26.363 --> 07:29.073
I borrowed it!
I borrowed a kid's bike.

07:29.157 --> 07:30.742
And I got my packages
delivered, and that is

07:30.743 --> 07:32.326
what you people are gonna
have to start doing.

07:32.410 --> 07:35.955
You have to start doing whatever it takes,
because in three hours and two minutes...

07:36.039 --> 07:39.124
every one of these packages
has to be on the big truck...

07:39.209 --> 07:41.126
and on its way to the airport.

07:41.211 --> 07:43.754
Fifteen minutes!

07:43.838 --> 07:47.132
- Crunch time! Crunch time!
- Crunch time!

07:47.217 --> 07:50.469
Let's go! Every package
on the airport truck.

07:50.553 --> 07:52.638
Go! Crunch, crunch, crunch!

07:52.722 --> 07:54.640
- We have a big problem.
- What?

07:54.724 --> 07:57.434
- The truck in Red Square is stuck.
- What do you mean?

07:57.519 --> 08:00.145
- It's stuck.
- Stuck how? In snow? In ice?

08:00.230 --> 08:03.732
It's stuck! The most important truck...
the Kremlin truck! Many packages.

08:13.743 --> 08:16.078
All right, all right, all right.
Let's put the table right here.

08:16.162 --> 08:18.080
We'll just do the sort.

08:18.164 --> 08:21.333
Ah, yeah, a clamp.
That would make us stuck.

08:21.418 --> 08:24.003
Let's go. Unload...
Get him out of there.

08:24.087 --> 08:26.630
Right here.
Two lines, two lines.

08:26.715 --> 08:29.591
One to the airport truck,
one to the Moscow truck.

08:29.676 --> 08:31.343
Got it?

08:31.428 --> 08:35.014
C.D.G., F.E., M.E, Memphis on the airport
truck. Everything else right there.

08:35.097 --> 08:37.765
Nicolai! Tick-tock, tick-tock.
Four minutes.

08:40.102 --> 08:42.688
- Hi, this is Kelly.
- If you're calling for Chuck, press one.

08:42.772 --> 08:44.940
Otherwise leave a message
after the tone. Thanks.

08:45.025 --> 08:47.026
Hello, Kelly. Are you there?

08:47.110 --> 08:49.611
Pick up, pick up, pick up,
pick up. You're not there.

08:49.696 --> 08:52.698
You're not gonna believe this. I'm doin'
the sorts in the middle of Red Square...

08:52.782 --> 08:54.700
in the shadow of Lenin's tomb.

08:58.913 --> 09:01.749
I'm outta here in two minutes and I'm
pickin' up the sweep through Paris...

09:01.833 --> 09:04.418
so I should be back in Memphis
about 18 hours or so.

09:04.502 --> 09:06.628
That's the good news.
The bad news is...

09:06.713 --> 09:08.630
I gotta go to
the dentist this week.

09:08.715 --> 09:10.674
I got something in there
that's hurtin'.

09:10.759 --> 09:13.552
I love you and I'm gonna see you soon,
and you know what that means.

09:13.636 --> 09:16.305
Bye-bye. Nicolai! Tick-tock, tick-tock,
tick-tock, tick-tock!

09:35.868 --> 09:37.826
I absolutely, positively have
to get to Memphis tonight.

09:37.911 --> 09:39.953
Can't help you. Try U.P.S.

09:40.038 --> 09:42.706
With this extra head wind, are we gonna
be able to push it and make the sort?

09:42.791 --> 09:45.167
- We'll do our best.
- "Our best," huh?

09:45.251 --> 09:47.378
Gwen, is there something
wrong with our doctors

09:47.379 --> 09:49.505
that Jack keeps getting
certified to fly?

09:49.589 --> 09:51.924
- Aren't you concerned?
- I'm terrified.

09:52.008 --> 09:53.967
But a girl's gotta do
what a girl's gotta do.

09:54.052 --> 09:56.929
That's the spirit.
Relentless is our goal. Relentless!

09:57.013 --> 10:00.182
What do you expect from the guy
who stole a crippled kid's bicycle...

10:00.266 --> 10:02.601
- when his truck broke down?
- I borrowed it.

10:02.685 --> 10:04.812
But I love that
the kid's now crippled.

10:04.896 --> 10:07.397
So you missed the last truck
by two minutes?

10:07.482 --> 10:10.359
Two minutes.
Actually, it was less than that.

10:10.443 --> 10:13.362
The plane wasn't that heavy.
You could've added some fuel...

10:13.446 --> 10:15.364
picked up the speed
and made up the time.

10:15.448 --> 10:18.617
It's about the trucks.
Today's truck was two minutes late.

10:18.701 --> 10:21.703
Tomorrow's will be four minutes late, and
then six minutes and eight minutes late.

10:21.788 --> 10:25.791
- Next thing you know, we're the U.S. Mail.
- Yeah, well...

10:25.875 --> 10:28.377
All I'm sayin' is, if you'd gotten
all those trucks on the plane...

10:28.461 --> 10:31.213
those Russkies would be
walking on water right now.

10:31.297 --> 10:33.757
Hey, don't...
Don't gimme that look.

10:33.842 --> 10:36.301
- It's just grape juice. Right, Chuck?
- Yeah.

10:36.386 --> 10:39.471
It's like a 1992
full-bodied grape juice.

10:39.556 --> 10:41.807
I see no evil, hear no evil,
speak no evil.

10:41.891 --> 10:45.227
We'd offer you some but, you know,
somebody's got to fly the plane.

10:45.311 --> 10:48.772
Yeah, well,
I "just say no," right?

10:48.857 --> 10:51.650
Listen, Stan,
I've been meaning to ask you.

10:51.734 --> 10:53.777
How's Mary?

10:53.862 --> 10:57.156
Oh. Uh, well...

10:57.240 --> 11:00.325
- we really don't know anything yet.
- Mm-hmm.

11:00.410 --> 11:05.289
Uh, she went to the doctor yesterday,
and, uh...

11:05.373 --> 11:09.168
it hasn't meta...
metastasized...

11:09.252 --> 11:12.212
as far as they
can tell right now.

11:12.297 --> 11:15.215
It's just kind of wait and see.

11:15.300 --> 11:17.509
I'm so sorry.

11:17.594 --> 11:20.804
Tell her I'm gonna come by
and see her on my next layover.

11:20.889 --> 11:24.183
I want you to know, Stan, we are
all thinking about her and you.

11:24.267 --> 11:26.977
- And just blessings.
- Thank you, Gwen.

11:27.061 --> 11:29.688
Hi, this is Kelly.
If you're calling for Chuck, press one.

11:29.772 --> 11:32.691
Otherwise, leave a message
after the tone. Thanks.

11:37.947 --> 11:40.657
Stan.

11:40.742 --> 11:43.202
Listen.
Uh, I heard about this...

11:44.954 --> 11:48.165
I heard about this doctor
down in Emory, in Atlanta.

11:48.249 --> 11:50.167
Uh, he's supposed to be
the absolute best.

11:50.251 --> 11:52.336
He worked on
Frank Toretta's wife.

11:52.420 --> 11:54.338
Frank Toretta is
a systems analyst.

11:54.422 --> 11:56.882
He played center field for us.
You know him.

11:56.966 --> 11:59.635
In the softball tournament
last Labor Day.

11:59.719 --> 12:01.553
Anyway, beside the point.

12:01.638 --> 12:06.225
Uh, what I was thinking is,
is that I could get his number...

12:06.309 --> 12:08.894
the doctor... and, uh...

12:08.978 --> 12:11.480
you know,
put you all together and...

12:12.982 --> 12:15.400
You know, you could
get this thing fixed.

12:15.485 --> 12:17.444
You could beat it.

12:18.738 --> 12:20.697
Thanks, Chuck.

12:20.782 --> 12:23.242
So, I'll get his number.

12:45.640 --> 12:49.559
- Is Kelly Frears around?
- She's copying her dissertation.

13:21.050 --> 13:23.427
- You're home.
- Home indeed.

13:23.511 --> 13:25.429
I love that you're home.

13:43.406 --> 13:45.992
Just days before Santa

13:45.993 --> 13:48.577
departs on his annual
gift-giving venture...

13:48.661 --> 13:51.580
he's been declared
physically fit to fly.

13:51.664 --> 13:55.500
Santa got checked out by doctors
at the V.A. Hospital in Augusta, Georgia.

13:55.585 --> 13:58.420
After they declared
the jolly old elf in tiptop shape...

13:58.504 --> 14:02.007
Santa Claus took off into the wild
blue yonder for an early start.

14:02.091 --> 14:04.593
In Sarajevo,
he spent the day with children...

14:04.677 --> 14:07.512
handing out presents and
even helping them decorate...

14:07.597 --> 14:09.556
the special Christmas tree.

14:13.686 --> 14:16.063
Santa and a sea of elves
took over the floor...

14:16.147 --> 14:18.065
at the Hong Kong
Futures Exchange.

14:18.149 --> 14:20.525
Market traders
bought Santa hats, donating...

14:43.091 --> 14:45.050
The turkey's a little dry,
isn't it?

14:45.134 --> 14:47.636
- No.
- The turkey is perfect.

14:51.474 --> 14:54.726
- How many did you do last night?
- Last night? 2.9 million.

14:54.811 --> 14:58.397
Now you've got to be in the market
for more of these candied yams.

14:58.481 --> 14:59.898
Here you go.

14:59.982 --> 15:01.942
2.9 has got to be the record.

15:02.026 --> 15:03.944
Look at those marshmallows.

15:04.028 --> 15:06.029
When I was there,
we did two million.

15:06.114 --> 15:08.615
- We thought that was a big deal.
- The glory days.

15:08.699 --> 15:11.243
- What'd they do the first night?
- The very first night?

15:11.327 --> 15:13.245
- Twelve.
- Twelve thousand?

15:13.329 --> 15:15.997
- Hell, no. Twelve.
- That's right.

15:16.082 --> 15:18.834
And they did the sort
right there on a card table.

15:18.918 --> 15:21.628
And Fred Smith had
that card table bronzed.

15:21.712 --> 15:24.423
I've been hearing that
for five years.

15:24.507 --> 15:26.592
It's in his office today.

15:26.593 --> 15:28.677
They go from that to the
new hub up in Anchorage.

15:28.761 --> 15:30.679
It's state of the art...
a perfect marriage...

15:30.763 --> 15:33.223
between technology
and systems management.

15:33.307 --> 15:36.059
Speaking of marriage, Chuck, when are you
gonna make an honest woman out of Kelly?

15:38.479 --> 15:41.314
- How long?
- Fourteen minutes into the meal.

15:41.399 --> 15:44.651
- You won. I owe you $5.
- So I win.

15:44.735 --> 15:46.736
- Way before the pie.
- I told him on the way up.

15:46.821 --> 15:49.948
Right about the time the pie
came out, the marriage...

15:50.032 --> 15:53.034
Kelly is still recovering from her failed
relationship with that parolee.

15:53.119 --> 15:55.287
He was a lawyer.

15:55.371 --> 15:57.622
I knew it had something to do
with raising your right hand...

15:57.707 --> 15:59.624
and swearing to tell the truth.

15:59.709 --> 16:01.252
Remember when he fell
on the sidewalk and

16:01.253 --> 16:02.794
broke his shoulder at
the wedding reception?

16:02.879 --> 16:05.630
He tripped on a curb
holding a door open for me.

16:05.715 --> 16:09.050
- Aunt Kelly was married before?
- It's not even worth remembering.

16:09.135 --> 16:12.012
So since her failed marriage
to the parolee...

16:12.096 --> 16:14.598
Oh, my God.

16:14.599 --> 16:17.100
Kelly can't see being with a
man who wears a pager to bed.

16:17.185 --> 16:19.144
What're you gonna
attach it to, Hoss?

16:19.228 --> 16:22.105
When you wear it to bed, I hope
you got one of those things...

16:22.190 --> 16:24.024
that go vibratin'.

16:24.108 --> 16:26.526
Watch it.
I'm not touching that.

16:26.611 --> 16:29.988
Oh, did you hit an olive pit?

16:30.072 --> 16:34.326
- I thought I took all of them out.
- No, no, it's not that.

17:00.686 --> 17:02.938
- Okay, I'll cancel Saturday.
- No, don't.

17:03.022 --> 17:04.940
If I'm not here, I'm not.
But if I am, well...

17:05.023 --> 17:06.942
- then I am.
- It's cancelled.

17:07.026 --> 17:08.944
But you gotta be here
New Year's Eve.

17:09.028 --> 17:11.445
Malaysia can't be that bad.
I'll be here New Year's Eve.

17:11.531 --> 17:13.990
- When are you defending your dissertation?
- January 12.

17:14.075 --> 17:18.494
I'm gonna have to switch
over the South America thing.

17:18.579 --> 17:20.914
If I do that
on the third or fourth...

17:20.998 --> 17:22.915
I'm gonna have to head
back out on the 13th.

17:23.000 --> 17:25.210
So long as you're here
New Year's Eve.

17:25.294 --> 17:28.296
I will be here New Year's Eve.
I promise.

17:31.592 --> 17:33.782
What?

17:33.783 --> 17:35.971
What about our Christmas?
I got a gift for you.

17:38.641 --> 17:41.184
We have to do it in the car.

17:46.482 --> 17:49.568
I'd just like a minute
over here, all right? Thanks.

17:56.158 --> 17:58.493
Two minutes, okay?

17:58.578 --> 18:01.121
Two more minutes. Thanks. Hey!

18:01.205 --> 18:03.665
- Merry Christmas.
- I thought you were gonna stiff me.

18:03.749 --> 18:05.146
No.

18:05.147 --> 18:06.543
- What is the ribbon?
Is it a thousand-pound...

18:06.627 --> 18:09.963
- test fishing line or something?
- Here's your fancy thing.

18:10.047 --> 18:12.799
Thanks.

18:15.678 --> 18:17.846
I love the wrapping.

18:19.473 --> 18:21.474
- And I love the box.
- Good.

18:24.186 --> 18:28.231
Oh. Oh, my.

18:29.358 --> 18:31.276
Oh, that is terrific.

18:31.360 --> 18:33.862
My grandaddy used it
on the Southern Pacific.

18:36.532 --> 18:40.535
Hey, I took this. This is
my favorite picture of you.

18:42.163 --> 18:45.081
You know what I'm gonna do?
I'm always gonna keep this...

18:45.166 --> 18:47.876
on Memphis time.

18:50.713 --> 18:52.631
Kelly time.

18:52.715 --> 18:54.758
Hmm.

18:54.842 --> 18:56.801
You haven't said anything about
your presents. Is there a problem?

18:56.886 --> 18:58.970
I'm sorry, no! I love 'em.

18:59.055 --> 19:01.264
Look at my journal. Ah!

19:01.349 --> 19:05.101
- What about the pager?
- Real leather. The pages have gold on 'em.

19:05.186 --> 19:07.228
- Did you like the pager or not?
- Yes.

19:07.313 --> 19:11.066
I love it. Look at him in
his little blue Russian house.

19:11.150 --> 19:14.027
- It's from Russia.
- My God.

19:14.111 --> 19:17.572
- It's not one of those loud ones?
- No. You can program it so it vibrates...

19:17.657 --> 19:20.241
and lights up
and see it in the dark.

19:20.326 --> 19:24.371
It seems like
a real nice pager.

19:24.455 --> 19:26.290
Sorry about the hand towels.
You're hard to shop for.

19:26.291 --> 19:28.124
No, no. I love 'em.

19:28.209 --> 19:30.231
Every time I wash my hands,
I will think of you.

19:30.232 --> 19:32.253
All right, I gotta go.

19:32.338 --> 19:36.257
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

19:36.342 --> 19:38.259
- I love you.
- I love you too.

19:45.810 --> 19:48.603
Chuck! Keys!

19:58.531 --> 20:01.658
- Thank you.
- That reminds me. I almost forgot.

20:01.742 --> 20:05.161
I have one more present
for you.

20:05.246 --> 20:10.375
Only this isn't an "open in the car"
kind of present...

20:10.459 --> 20:12.377
like, say, hand towels.

20:12.461 --> 20:14.921
Which were a joke, by the way.

20:19.135 --> 20:21.678
I'm terrified.

20:21.762 --> 20:24.848
Just take it and hold onto it,
and you can open it...

20:24.932 --> 20:27.559
on New Year's Eve.

20:27.643 --> 20:29.602
And I love you.

20:33.399 --> 20:36.151
I'll be right back.

21:20.070 --> 21:22.614
Hey, Al, where are we?

21:22.698 --> 21:24.657
Somewhere over
the Pacific Ocean.

21:24.742 --> 21:27.285
Ha, ha, ha!
You pilots, you're funny.

21:27.369 --> 21:29.662
Tahiti Control, FedEx 88.

21:29.747 --> 21:32.582
Position Jenna at 1526...

21:32.666 --> 21:35.627
Is all this turbulence from Santa
and those eight tiny reindeer?

21:35.711 --> 21:38.296
Tamara at 1620.

21:38.380 --> 21:40.632
Erick is next.

21:40.716 --> 21:43.343
Fuel: niner-five-decimal-five.

21:43.427 --> 21:45.678
Blaine, tell them we're
deviating south for weather.

21:45.763 --> 21:48.139
Make another position plot
on your deviation left.

21:48.224 --> 21:50.642
Tahiti Control,
FedEx 88.

21:50.726 --> 21:53.394
Position Jenna at 1526.

21:53.479 --> 21:55.855
- Flight level 350.
- I got us plotted.

21:55.940 --> 21:58.858
We're 200 miles south
of our original course.

21:58.943 --> 22:01.653
Continue plotting,
and check contingency procedures.

22:01.737 --> 22:03.696
Tahiti Control, FedEx 88.

22:03.781 --> 22:06.199
Broadcasting in the blind.
How do you read?

22:07.493 --> 22:08.701
I've never been
out of comm this long.

22:08.786 --> 22:11.830
Did you try the higher
H.F. frequency?

22:11.914 --> 22:14.374
Tahiti Control, FedEx 88.

22:14.458 --> 22:17.377
Better buckle up, Chuck.
It's gonna get bumpy.

22:17.461 --> 22:20.296
Tahiti Control, FedEx 88.

22:20.381 --> 22:22.465
Do you read?

22:31.016 --> 22:33.017
Tahiti Control, FedEx 88.

22:33.102 --> 22:36.020
Position Jenna at 1526.

22:36.105 --> 22:38.147
Flight level 350.

22:38.232 --> 22:40.149
Expecting Tamara at 1...

